doc.after: High accuracy time keeping low earth orbit satellite tracking and pulsar timing are applications that require the consideration of the combined effects of mass and motion in producing time dilation Practical examples include the International Atomic Time standard and its relationship with the Barycentric Coordinate Time standard used for interplanetary objects
